HEADWORD: Amphigory
<hw>Am"phi*go*ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>amphigouri</ets>, of uncertain derivation; perh. fr. Gr.
<grk>'amfi`</grk> + <?/ a circle.]</ety> <def>A nonsense verse; a
rigmarole, with apparent meaning, which on further attention proves to
be meaningless.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>amphigouri</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

